Mario &amp; Luigi: Partners in Time, known in Japan as Mario &amp; Luigi RPG 2 (マリオ&amp;ルイージRPG2, Mario ando Ruīji Ārupījī Tsū), is a console role-playing game developed by AlphaDream and published by Nintendo for the Nintendo DS video game console in 2005.
A successor to the game, Mario &amp; Luigi 3, has been scheduled for release in 2009.
Nintendo revealed Partners in Time at the E3 conference of 2005, where a playable demonstration of the game was available.
